Her head hung low as she left the principals office. "Dads going to kill me she" she murmured under her breath as she hesitantly started to walk towards the classroom. The dust drifted through the air in the ancient sun lit corridors. The oak floorboards under her squeaked as she peaked into an empty classroom. The room seemed more like a cell than anywhere learning could possible take place as the barred windows gave a grim feel to the room. The steel chairs glistened with a cold sheen, shivering her out of her daze. As she strolled on on she noticed how the doors on the prehistoric lockers were covered with human sized dents.
